#! <SUBDOCUMENTS>
#! <SUBDOCUMENT
#!   NAME="BGT-downloader"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY=""
#!   CATEGORY="Web"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;h1&gt;BGT-downloader&lt;/h1&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Terralytics (Koen Verhoeven)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;PDOK provides an API to download the BGT (Basisadministratie Grootschalige Topografie).&#10;You can find the API over here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://api.pdok.nl/lv/bgt/download/v1_0/ui/&quot;&gt;https://api.pdok.nl/lv/bgt/download/v1_0/ui/&#10;&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;With this transformer &quot;BGT-downloader&quot; you can download the data using your own geometry as input. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hint&lt;/strong&gt;:&#10;To minimize the amount of API-requests, try to aggregate your data before it enters the BGT-downloader.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Input&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;The transformer expects polygons as input data. For each polygon entering the transformer, a BGT-download will be returned for that area and some buffer around it. This buffer is created by the API, not by this transformer.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Data formats&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;The transformer provides three formats:&#10;1. CityGML. This is the standard format with most options. When downloading deltas/mutations this is your only option. CityGML also contains expired/historic objects.&#10;2. GMLLight. It is a lighter GML-format with less options. It contains expired/historic objects. &#10;3. StUF-Geo. This format contains the BGT data using the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.geonovum.nl/geo-standaarden/bgt-imgeo/berichtencatalogus-stuf-geo-imgeo-versie-13&quot;&gt;StUF-Geo format.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Parameter settings&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Format: choose for one of the three data formats described above.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Feature types: choose the feature types you would like to download. By default alle feature types except &apos;Plaatsbepalingspunten&apos; are selected.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Only mutations after date: For the CityGML format it is possible to download the deltas. This means only objects after a given date will be returned by the API. Use the setting &apos;mutations after date&apos; to select the startdate of the mutations you need. &lt;strong&gt;Important&lt;/strong&gt;: Deltas are only available for last month and until the day before yesterday. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Output folder: Choose the directory where the download will be saved&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Output Filename: By default the filename will be generated automatically. You can override this by typing your own value. Make sure the filename ends with .zip&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Output ports&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Zip-Filepath: Returns the location of the downloaded zip-file.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Rejected: Returns rejected features. Check logfile for the reason of rejection.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Process data&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;In one of the earlier versions the transformer also contained options to process the data. To improve the usability of the transformer, the processing moved to a new, separate transformer, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://hub.safe.com/publishers/terralytics/transformers/bgt-processor&quot;&gt;BGT-processor&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Credits&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;The BGT-downloader is used a lot! Because of that I also received a lot of feedback for improvements:&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Jan Droesen (Movares): Jan sent me his example of a custom transformer for processing the data. (v2) &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Michiel Faber (IDgis): Michiel gave feedback for improving the speed of the request status of the download. (v1.1)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Evelien Droge (Cobra groeninzicht): Evelien helped me with testing and provided some useful feedback. (v1)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Lars de Vries (Omkeere) for the idea to add the GML-axis order to avoid invalid geometry. (v2.3)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Pieter-Jan Demmers (Gemeente Heusden): Pieter-Jan gave me a lot of input, especially concerning the OpenbareRuimteLabels (v3)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Hans Pouw (Defensie Pijplijn Organisatie): Together with Hans we improved the transformer by using it as part of a bigger project. This resulted in many smaller improvements (v3)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Thanks for all the feedback! &lt;/p&gt;"
#!   DOC_DYNAMIC_INPUT_ATTRS="0"
#!   DOC_EXTENTS="19175.9 3114.64"
#!   DOC_TOP_LEFT="-9332.29 -1798.1"
#!   FME_DOCUMENT_GUID="b8f5570e-8f27-4f2a-8db5-e3fa60cafcc1"
#!   FME_DOCUMENT_PRIORGUID=""
#!   FME_NAMES_ENCODING="windows-1252"
#!   FME_PROCESS_COUNT="NO_PARALLELISM"
#!   FME_PROCESS_GROUPS_ORDERED="No"
#!   FME_PROCESS_GROUP_BY=""
#!   FME_PROCESS_PRESERVE_GROUP_ATTR="No"
#!   FMX_ATTRIBUTE_PROPOGATION_MODE="AUTO"
#!   GUID="b8f5570e-8f27-4f2a-8db5-e3fa60cafcc1"
#!   HISTORY="28-1-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v01,28-1-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v02&lt;space&gt;Fixed&lt;space&gt;bug&lt;space&gt;with&lt;space&gt;features&lt;space&gt;parameter&lt;space&gt;Choice&lt;space&gt;with&lt;space&gt;alias&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Multiple&lt;closeparen&gt;,29-1-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v1&lt;space&gt;Added&lt;space&gt;some&lt;space&gt;functionality&lt;space&gt;to&lt;space&gt;make&lt;space&gt;the&lt;space&gt;transformer&lt;space&gt;more&lt;space&gt;stable,07-4-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v1.1&lt;space&gt;Now&lt;space&gt;checking&lt;space&gt;the&lt;space&gt;request&lt;space&gt;status&lt;space&gt;every&lt;space&gt;second&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;instead&lt;space&gt;of&lt;space&gt;an&lt;space&gt;incremental&lt;space&gt;time&lt;space&gt;interval&lt;closeparen&gt;,4-5-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v2&lt;space&gt;Added&lt;space&gt;functionality&lt;space&gt;for&lt;space&gt;processing&lt;space&gt;the&lt;space&gt;data&lt;space&gt;,6-5-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v2.1&lt;space&gt;Set&lt;space&gt;coordinate&lt;space&gt;system&lt;space&gt;of&lt;space&gt;processed&lt;space&gt;data&lt;space&gt;on&lt;space&gt;EPSG:28992.&lt;space&gt;Prevailing&lt;space&gt;changed&lt;space&gt;in&lt;space&gt;Present,11-5-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v2.2&lt;space&gt;New&lt;space&gt;PDOK&lt;space&gt;download&lt;space&gt;Url,15-5-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v2.3&lt;space&gt;Added&lt;space&gt;GML&lt;space&gt;Axis&lt;space&gt;order&lt;space&gt;to&lt;space&gt;avoid&lt;space&gt;invalid&lt;space&gt;geometry,31-12-2020,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v3.0&lt;space&gt;Multiple&lt;space&gt;changes:&lt;space&gt;StUF-Geo&lt;space&gt;processing&lt;comma&gt;&lt;space&gt;OpenbareRuimteLabel&lt;space&gt;processing&lt;comma&gt;&lt;space&gt;improved&lt;space&gt;filtering&lt;space&gt;current&lt;space&gt;objects&lt;comma&gt;&lt;space&gt;new&lt;space&gt;option&lt;space&gt;to&lt;space&gt;process&lt;space&gt;existing&lt;space&gt;downloads&lt;comma&gt;&lt;space&gt;etc.,16-4-2021,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v3.1&lt;space&gt;Added&lt;space&gt;new&lt;space&gt;option&lt;space&gt;for&lt;space&gt;delta&lt;space&gt;downloads,20-4-2021,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v3.2&lt;space&gt;Changed&lt;space&gt;preprod&lt;space&gt;URL&lt;space&gt;to&lt;space&gt;prod&lt;space&gt;URL,22-12-2021,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v4.0&lt;space&gt;Divided&lt;space&gt;BGT&lt;space&gt;download&lt;space&gt;and&lt;space&gt;processing&lt;space&gt;in&lt;space&gt;two&lt;space&gt;separate&lt;space&gt;custom&lt;space&gt;transformers,8-6-2022,Koen&lt;space&gt;Verhoeven&lt;space&gt;&lt;openparen&gt;Terralytics&lt;closeparen&gt;,v4.1&lt;space&gt;Fixed&lt;space&gt;citygml&lt;space&gt;format&lt;space&gt;for&lt;space&gt;delta-download&lt;space&gt;and&lt;space&gt;some&lt;space&gt;geometry&lt;space&gt;checks"
#!   IS_VISIBLE="true"
#!   LAST_SAVE_BUILD="FME(R) 2019.2.3.2 (20200320 - Build 19825 - WIN64)"
#!   LAST_SAVE_DATE="2022-06-08T09:02:06"
#!   MARKDOWN_DESCRIPTION="#BGT-downloader&#10;_Terralytics (Koen Verhoeven)_&#10;&#10;PDOK provides an API to download the BGT (Basisadministratie Grootschalige Topografie).&#10;You can find the API over here: [https://api.pdok.nl/lv/bgt/download/v1_0/ui/&#10;](https://api.pdok.nl/lv/bgt/download/v1_0/ui/)  &#10;&#10;With this transformer &quot;BGT-downloader&quot; you can download the data using your own geometry as input. &#10;&#10;**Hint**:&#10;To minimize the amount of API-requests, try to aggregate your data before it enters the BGT-downloader.&#10;&#10;###Input###&#10;The transformer expects polygons as input data. For each polygon entering the transformer, a BGT-download will be returned for that area and some buffer around it. This buffer is created by the API, not by this transformer.&#10;&#10;###Data formats###&#10;The transformer provides three formats:&#10;1. CityGML. This is the standard format with most options. When downloading deltas/mutations this is your only option. CityGML also contains expired/historic objects.&#10;2. GMLLight. It is a lighter GML-format with less options. It contains expired/historic objects. &#10;3. StUF-Geo. This format contains the BGT data using the [StUF-Geo format.](https://www.geonovum.nl/geo-standaarden/bgt-imgeo/berichtencatalogus-stuf-geo-imgeo-versie-13)&#10;&#10;&#10;###Parameter settings###&#10;- Format: choose for one of the three data formats described above.&#10;- Feature types: choose the feature types you would like to download. By default alle feature types except &apos;Plaatsbepalingspunten&apos; are selected.&#10;- Only mutations after date: For the CityGML format it is possible to download the deltas. This means only objects after a given date will be returned by the API. Use the setting &apos;mutations after date&apos; to select the startdate of the mutations you need. **Important**: Deltas are only available for last month and until the day before yesterday. &#10;- Output folder: Choose the directory where the download will be saved&#10;- Output Filename: By default the filename will be generated automatically. You can override this by typing your own value. Make sure the filename ends with .zip&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;###Output ports###&#10;&#10;- Zip-Filepath: Returns the location of the downloaded zip-file.&#10;- Rejected: Returns rejected features. Check logfile for the reason of rejection.&#10;&#10;###Process data###&#10;In one of the earlier versions the transformer also contained options to process the data. To improve the usability of the transformer, the processing moved to a new, separate transformer, the [BGT-processor](https://hub.safe.com/publishers/terralytics/transformers/bgt-processor). &#10;&#10;###Credits&#10;&#10;The BGT-downloader is used a lot! Because of that I also received a lot of feedback for improvements:&#10;&#10;- Jan Droesen (Movares): Jan sent me his example of a custom transformer for processing the data. (v2) &#10;- Michiel Faber (IDgis): Michiel gave feedback for improving the speed of the request status of the download. (v1.1)&#10;- Evelien Droge (Cobra groeninzicht): Evelien helped me with testing and provided some useful feedback. (v1)&#10;- Lars de Vries (Omkeere) for the idea to add the GML-axis order to avoid invalid geometry. (v2.3)&#10;- Pieter-Jan Demmers (Gemeente Heusden): Pieter-Jan gave me a lot of input, especially concerning the OpenbareRuimteLabels (v3)&#10;- Hans Pouw (Defensie Pijplijn Organisatie): Together with Hans we improved the transformer by using it as part of a bigger project. This resulted in many smaller improvements (v3)&#10;&#10;Thanks for all the feedback! &#10;"
#!   MARKDOWN_USAGE=""
