#! <SUBDOCUMENT
#!   NAME="BGT-processor"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY=""
#!   CATEGORY="Web"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;h1&gt;BGT-processor&lt;/h1&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Terralytics (Koen Verhoeven)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This transformer processes a previously downloaded BGT ZIP-file. The BGT can be downloaded using the custom transformer&lt;a href=&quot;https://hub.safe.com/publishers/terralytics/transformers/bgt-downloader&quot;&gt; BGT-downloader&lt;/a&gt; or directly using the &lt;a href=&quot;https://api.pdok.nl/lv/bgt/download/v1_0/ui/&quot;&gt;PDOK BGT API&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Input&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;The transformer expects a path to a ZIP-file containing a BGT-download. The ZIP-file may contain CityGML-files, GMLLight files or StUF-Geo files. The type of file is recognized automatically.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Parameter settings&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;BGT download ZIP-file path: the path to a ZIP-file containing a BGT-download. By default the response file path of the BGT-downloader is used.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Feature types:  choose the feature types you would like to process. By default all feature types within the download are processed.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Process options:&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Expose and rename common attributes: When set, the transformer will rename and expose the most common attributes. Not all attributes are exposed and renamed. So check the data with the inspector if you miss some attributes for your own process. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Process kruinlijnen: Kruinlijnen are the highest point of an area on a slope (Talud). By default, kruinlijnen are a geometry collection with the area on the slope. When this option is set, the geometry collections are split into a line (Kruinlijn) and polygon.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Only current objects: If selected, the transformer only returns existing, active objects. So basically everything you would like to see on a map as the current situation. When the StUF-GEO format is used it only returns the &apos;Wordt&apos; objects (and no &apos;Was&apos;) objects.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Spatial filter: The PDOK API by default returns a bigger area than requested. So in most cases the data needs to be filtered. The spatial filter by default returns all objects which intersect with the intiator/input. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;h3&gt;Output ports&lt;/h3&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;SchemaFeatures: Returns the schema for all formats&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;RawData: Returns the downloaded objects without exposing and renaming attributes. The RawData is always returned.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Processed: Returns the downloaded objects after exposing and renaming the most common BGT-attributes. Not all attributes are exposed and renamed. So check the data with the inspector if you miss some attributes for your own process. &lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Rejected: Returns rejected features. Check logfile for the reason of rejection.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;"
#!   DOC_DYNAMIC_INPUT_ATTRS="0"
#!   DOC_EXTENTS="15845.1 3375.72"
#!   DOC_TOP_LEFT="-7279.08 -1663.23"
#!   FME_DOCUMENT_GUID=""
